bin/run tests/intro.vera --plast
--------------------------------------------------
The first character in a file assigns a spacer glyph.
A program is made of rules and facts.
Two spacers indicate the creation of facts
Facts are separated by commas
a warm fire
a box
==================================================
bin/run tests/salad.vera --plast
--------------------------------------------------
fruit cake
==================================================
bin/run tests/hello.vera --plast
--------------------------------------------------
a log
the door is open
wash dishes
sweep floors
get groceries
feed pets
==================================================
echo "||hello world" | bin/run --plast
--------------------------------------------------
hello world
==================================================
